The man found guilty of killing a UJ student will be sentenced in the High Court in Johannesburg this morning. Dumisani Mkhwanazi was found guilty of the 2013 murder of Palesa Madiba last December. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Dumisani Mkhwanazi will learn his fate on Friday in the High Court in Johannesburg. READ: Mpho Thobane sentenced to 20 years for girlfriend's murder Mkhwanazi was found guilty of killing University of Johannesburg (UJ) student Palesa Madiba in 2013. Dumisani Mkhwanazi will find out his fate in the High Court in Johannesburg on Friday. Mkhwanazi was found guilty of killing UJ student Palesa Madiba in 2013. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/fuHR2z4KVz Madiba went missing in 2013. Her body was found two years later in a shallow grave at a house in Phiri. Mkhwanazi lived in a back room of the property owned by his family. Before his arrest last year, his family had obtained a protection order against Madiba's family to prevent them from going to their house in an attempt to locate her body.